{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01R9EmaPdqVRTMbrjBwgK1KU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, given the heavy Spring MVC usage (Thymeleaf templates, form binding with `@ModelAttribute`, `BindingResult`, `WebDataBinder`, `@InitBinder`, `RedirectAttributes`, Spring Data Page/Pageable), the most pragmatic Quarkus migration approach is:\n\n1. Use **Quarkus Spring extensions** (`quarkus-spring-web`, `quarkus-spring-data-jpa`) for maximum compatibility\n2. Use **Quarkus Qute** templates instead of Thymeleaf (since Quarkus doesn't have great Thymeleaf support)\n3. Rewrite controllers as JAX-RS + Qute where Spring MVC features aren't supported\n\nLet me now create the new pom.xml:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":433,"cache_read_input_tokens":74687,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":433,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1863},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"7da73db6-227d-4f95-ad3f-092d29563574"}
