{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BBurGL3TLcvkRTacVqTp8L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Find Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <form action=\"/owners\" method=\"get\" class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"search-owner-form\">\n     6→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n     7→      <div class=\"control-group\" id=\"lastNameGroup\">\n     8→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Last name </label>\n     9→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    10→          <input class=\"form-control\" name=\"lastName\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"80\" value=\"{lastName ?: ''}\" />\n    11→          {#if error}\n    12→          <span class=\"help-inline\">\n    13→            <p>{error}</p>\n    14→          </span>\n    15→          {/if}\n    16→        </div>\n    17→      </div>\n    18→    </div>\n    19→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    20→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    21→        <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Find Owner</button>\n    22→      </div>\n    23→    </div>\n    24→\n    25→    <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"/owners/new\">Add Owner</a>\n    26→\n    27→  </form>\n    28→{/body}\n    29→{/include}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"657ee02e-3af7-426b-9cd6-acef96350427"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LRxB1hBxmRrbtMZgaAH9fW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owner Information</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  {#if message}\n     6→  <div class=\"alert alert-success\" id=\"success-message\">\n     7→    <span>{message}</span>\n     8→  </div>\n     9→  {/if}\n    10→\n    11→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    12→    <tr>\n    13→      <th>Name</th>\n    14→      <td><b>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</b></td>\n    15→    </tr>\n    16→    <tr>\n    17→      <th>Address</th>\n    18→      <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    19→    </tr>\n    20→    <tr>\n    21→      <th>City</th>\n    22→      <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→    </tr>\n    24→    <tr>\n    25→      <th>Telephone</th>\n    26→      <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    27→    </tr>\n    28→  </table>\n    29→\n    30→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/edit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Edit Owner</a>\n    31→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/new\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Add New Pet</a>\n    32→\n    33→  <br />\n    34→  <br />\n    35→  <br />\n    36→  <h2>Pets and Visits</h2>\n    37→\n    38→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    39→    {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    40→    <tr>\n    41→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    42→        <dl class=\"dl-horizontal\">\n    43→          <dt>Name</dt>\n    44→          <dd>{pet.name}</dd>\n    45→          <dt>Birth Date</dt>\n    46→          <dd>{pet.birthDate}</dd>\n    47→          <dt>Type</dt>\n    48→          <dd>{pet.type.name}</dd>\n    49→        </dl>\n    50→      </td>\n    51→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    52→        <table class=\"table-condensed\">\n    53→          <thead>\n    54→            <tr>\n    55→              <th>Visit Date</th>\n    56→              <th>Description</th>\n    57→            </tr>\n    58→          </thead>\n    59→          {#for visit in pet.visits}\n    60→          <tr>\n    61→            <td>{visit.date}</td>\n    62→            <td>{visit.description}</td>\n    63→          </tr>\n    64→          {/for}\n    65→          <tr>\n    66→            <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/edit\">Edit Pet</a></td>\n    67→            <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/visits/new\">Add Visit</a></td>\n    68→          </tr>\n    69→        </table>\n    70→      </td>\n    71→    </tr>\n    72→    {/for}\n    73→  </table>\n    74→{/body}\n    75→{/include}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"312d4182-66a9-4822-be44-17b13a20e6b9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SubrobN9URrvehfFket87G","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owner</h2>\n     4→  <form class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"add-owner-form\" method=\"post\">\n     5→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n     6→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n     7→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">First Name</label>\n     8→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n     9→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"firstName\" value=\"{owner.firstName ?: ''}\" />\n    10→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'firstName'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    11→        </div>\n    12→      </div>\n    13→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    14→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Last Name</label>\n    15→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    16→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"lastName\" value=\"{owner.lastName ?: ''}\" />\n    17→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'lastName'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    18→        </div>\n    19→      </div>\n    20→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    21→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Address</label>\n    22→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    23→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"address\" value=\"{owner.address ?: ''}\" />\n    24→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'address'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    25→        </div>\n    26→      </div>\n    27→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    28→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">City</label>\n    29→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    30→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"city\" value=\"{owner.city ?: ''}\" />\n    31→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'city'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    32→        </div>\n    33→      </div>\n    34→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    35→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Telephone</label>\n    36→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    37→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"telephone\" value=\"{owner.telephone ?: ''}\" />\n    38→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'telephone'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    39→        </div>\n    40→      </div>\n    41→    </div>\n    42→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    43→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    44→        <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{#if isNew}Add Owner{#else}Update Owner{/if}</button>\n    45→      </div>\n    46→    </div>\n    47→  </form>\n    48→{/body}\n    49→{/include}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"4b904ad6-c5bc-40d6-9793-2f1cfa04dd13"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QdVPeBTQB9wA4zoAMn4TVA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>{#if isNew}New {/if}Pet</h2>\n     4→  <form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n     5→    {#if pet.id}\n     6→    <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"{pet.id}\" />\n     7→    {/if}\n     8→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n     9→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    10→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Owner</label>\n    11→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    12→          <span>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</span>\n    13→        </div>\n    14→      </div>\n    15→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    16→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Name</label>\n    17→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    18→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"name\" value=\"{pet.name ?: ''}\" />\n    19→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'name'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    20→        </div>\n    21→      </div>\n    22→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    23→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Birth Date</label>\n    24→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    25→          <input type=\"date\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"birthDate\" value=\"{pet.birthDate ?: ''}\" />\n    26→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'birthDate'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    27→        </div>\n    28→      </div>\n    29→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    30→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Type</label>\n    31→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    32→          <select class=\"form-control\" name=\"typeId\">\n    33→            {#for type in types}\n    34→            <option value=\"{type.id}\" {#if pet.type != null}{#if pet.type.id == type.id}selected{/if}{/if}>{type.name}</option>\n    35→            {/for}\n    36→          </select>\n    37→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'type'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    38→        </div>\n    39→      </div>\n    40→    </div>\n    41→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    42→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    43→        <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{#if isNew}Add Pet{#else}Update Pet{/if}</button>\n    44→      </div>\n    45→    </div>\n    46→  </form>\n    47→{/body}\n    48→{/include}\n    49→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"8345b1a7-fdbd-4af4-b9c0-4ea219951c35"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T4Mvs9TRYCukQ4NYJHEesm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>New Visit</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <b>Pet</b>\n     6→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n     7→    <thead>\n     8→      <tr>\n     9→        <th>Name</th>\n    10→        <th>Birth Date</th>\n    11→        <th>Type</th>\n    12→        <th>Owner</th>\n    13→      </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tr>\n    16→      <td>{pet.name}</td>\n    17→      <td>{pet.birthDate}</td>\n    18→      <td>{pet.type.name}</td>\n    19→      <td>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</td>\n    20→    </tr>\n    21→  </table>\n    22→\n    23→  <form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n    24→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n    25→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    26→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Date</label>\n    27→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    28→          <input type=\"date\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"date\" value=\"{visit.date ?: ''}\" />\n    29→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'date'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    30→        </div>\n    31→      </div>\n    32→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    33→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Description</label>\n    34→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    35→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"description\" value=\"{visit.description ?: ''}\" />\n    36→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'description'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    37→        </div>\n    38→      </div>\n    39→    </div>\n    40→\n    41→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    42→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    43→        <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"petId\" value=\"{pet.id}\" />\n    44→        <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">Add Visit</button>\n    45→      </div>\n    46→    </div>\n    47→  </form>\n    48→\n    49→  <br />\n    50→  <b>Previous Visits</b>\n    51→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    52→    <tr>\n    53→      <th>Date</th>\n    54→      <th>Description</th>\n    55→    </tr>\n    56→    {#for v in pet.visits}\n    57→    <tr>\n    58→      <td>{v.date}</td>\n    59→      <td>{v.description}</td>\n    60→    </tr>\n    61→    {/for}\n    62→  </table>\n    63→{/body}\n    64→{/include}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"6155f12a-983d-4e89-b230-d13344481ad4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhjWr5ewWMYwnm6Ckn6ZkB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <table id=\"owners\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th style=\"width: 150px;\">Name</th>\n     9→        <th style=\"width: 200px;\">Address</th>\n    10→        <th>City</th>\n    11→        <th style=\"width: 120px\">Telephone</th>\n    12→        <th>Pets</th>\n    13→      </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tbody>\n    16→      {#for owner in listOwners}\n    17→      <tr>\n    18→        <td>\n    19→          <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}\">{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</a>\n    20→        </td>\n    21→        <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    22→        <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→        <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    24→        <td>{#for pet in owner.pets}{#if pet_count > 1}, {/if}{pet.name}{/for}</td>\n    25→      </tr>\n    26→      {/for}\n    27→    </tbody>\n    28→  </table>\n    29→  {#if totalPages > 1}\n    30→  <div>\n    31→    <span>Pages:</span>\n    32→    <span>[</span>\n    33→    {#for i in pages}\n    34→      {#if currentPage != i}\n    35→        <a href=\"/owners?page={i}&lastName={lastName ?: ''}\">{i}</a>\n    36→      {#else}\n    37→        <span>{i}</span>\n    38→      {/if}\n    39→    {/for}\n    40→    <span>]&nbsp;</span>\n    41→  </div>\n    42→  {/if}\n    43→{/body}\n    44→{/include}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"1bc78b00-9668-4