{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01M41nYVGfZF9km2GW9w4CgA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key fix is in Qute: `{#if error}` fails because `error` key doesn't exist in the template data map. In Qute, I need to use `{#if error??}` (the \"is-resolved\" operator) to check if a key exists. Also, for `{lastName ?: ''}` which also references keys not in the data map, I should add a default. Let me also fix the import.sql issue by not specifying explicit IDs.\n\nLet me fix the templates and Java code, and the import.sql:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6084,"cache_read_input_tokens":148743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6084,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":414},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"0e971d7a-4481-430f-9bb9-5026748aee19"}
