{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01McWJ8EkmobZtGqkkrmt9Cg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owner Information</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  {#if message}\n     6→  <div class=\"alert alert-success\" id=\"success-message\">\n     7→    <span>{message}</span>\n     8→  </div>\n     9→  {/if}\n    10→\n    11→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    12→    <tr>\n    13→      <th>Name</th>\n    14→      <td><b>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</b></td>\n    15→    </tr>\n    16→    <tr>\n    17→      <th>Address</th>\n    18→      <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    19→    </tr>\n    20→    <tr>\n    21→      <th>City</th>\n    22→      <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→    </tr>\n    24→    <tr>\n    25→      <th>Telephone</th>\n    26→      <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    27→    </tr>\n    28→  </table>\n    29→\n    30→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/edit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Edit Owner</a>\n    31→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/new\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Add New Pet</a>\n    32→\n    33→  <br />\n    34→  <br />\n    35→  <br />\n    36→  <h2>Pets and Visits</h2>\n    37→\n    38→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    39→    {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    40→    <tr>\n    41→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    42→        <dl class=\"dl-horizontal\">\n    43→          <dt>Name</dt>\n    44→          <dd>{pet.name}</dd>\n    45→          <dt>Birth Date</dt>\n    46→          <dd>{pet.birthDate}</dd>\n    47→          <dt>Type</dt>\n    48→          <dd>{pet.type.name}</dd>\n    49→        </dl>\n    50→      </td>\n    51→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    52→        <table class=\"table-condensed\">\n    53→          <thead>\n    54→            <tr>\n    55→              <th>Visit Date</th>\n    56→              <th>Description</th>\n    57→            </tr>\n    58→          </thead>\n    59→          {#for visit in pet.visits}\n    60→          <tr>\n    61→            <td>{visit.date}</td>\n    62→            <td>{visit.description}</td>\n    63→          </tr>\n    64→          {/for}\n    65→          <tr>\n    66→            <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/edit\">Edit Pet</a></td>\n    67→            <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/visits/new\">Add Visit</a></td>\n    68→          </tr>\n    69→        </table>\n    70→      </td>\n    71→    </tr>\n    72→    {/for}\n    73→  </table>\n    74→{/body}\n    75→{/include}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"4cb91043-eff1-4904-b395-b1f0387ea756"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016w7NQRPHruxP2TwPJVZ91E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owner</h2>\n     4→  <form class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"add-owner-form\" method=\"post\">\n     5→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n     6→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n     7→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">First Name</label>\n     8→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n     9→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"firstName\" value=\"{owner.firstName ?: ''}\" />\n    10→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'firstName'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    11→        </div>\n    12→      </div>\n    13→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    14→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Last Name</label>\n    15→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    16→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"lastName\" value=\"{owner.lastName ?: ''}\" />\n    17→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'lastName'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    18→        </div>\n    19→      </div>\n    20→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    21→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Address</label>\n    22→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    23→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"address\" value=\"{owner.address ?: ''}\" />\n    24→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'address'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    25→        </div>\n    26→      </div>\n    27→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    28→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">City</label>\n    29→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    30→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"city\" value=\"{owner.city ?: ''}\" />\n    31→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'city'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    32→        </div>\n    33→      </div>\n    34→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    35→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">Telephone</label>\n    36→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    37→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"telephone\" value=\"{owner.telephone ?: ''}\" />\n    38→          {#if errors}{#for e in errors}{#if e.field == 'telephone'}<span class=\"help-inline text-danger\">{e.message}</span>{/if}{/for}{/if}\n    39→        </div>\n    40→      </div>\n    41→    </div>\n    42→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    43→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    44→        <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{#if isNew}Add Owner{#else}Update Owner{/if}</button>\n    45→      </div>\n    46→    </div>\n    47→  </form>\n    48→{/body}\n    49→{/include}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"d1578d30-93a6-44f8-a7a7-5ecb1810dd9b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E7dBPX5GHtXdzsYVz9vH8M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <table id=\"owners\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th style=\"width: 150px;\">Name</th>\n     9→        <th style=\"width: 200px;\">Address</th>\n    10→        <th>City</th>\n    11→        <th style=\"width: 120px\">Telephone</th>\n    12→        <th>Pets</th>\n    13→      </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tbody>\n    16→      {#for owner in listOwners}\n    17→      <tr>\n    18→        <td>\n    19→          <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}\">{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</a>\n    20→        </td>\n    21→        <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    22→        <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→        <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    24→        <td>{#for pet in owner.pets}{#if pet_count > 1}, {/if}{pet.name}{/for}</td>\n    25→      </tr>\n    26→      {/for}\n    27→    </tbody>\n    28→  </table>\n    29→  {#if totalPages > 1}\n    30→  <div>\n    31→    <span>Pages:</span>\n    32→    <span>[</span>\n    33→    {#for i in pages}\n    34→      {#if currentPage != i}\n    35→        <a href=\"/owners?page={i}&lastName={lastName ?: ''}\">{i}</a>\n    36→      {#else}\n    37→        <span>{i}</span>\n    38→      {/if}\n    39→    {/for}\n    40→    <span>]&nbsp;</span>\n    41→  </div>\n    42→  {/if}\n    43→{/body}\n    44→{/include}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"23d86ead-62c5-4b16-b3aa-9b4eabc6c83d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SJLuxDXGHjnZV4QRz9WLZj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→-- Veterinarians\n     2→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (1, 'James', 'Carter');\n     3→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (2, 'Helen', 'Leary');\n     4→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (3, 'Linda', 'Douglas');\n     5→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (4, 'Rafael', 'Ortega');\n     6→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (5, 'Henry', 'Stevens');\n     7→INSERT INTO vets (id, first_name, last_name) VALUES (6, 'Sharon', 'Jenkins');\n     8→\n     9→-- Specialties\n    10→INSERT INTO specialties (id, name) VALUES (1, 'radiology');\n    11→INSERT INTO specialties (id, name) VALUES (2, 'surgery');\n    12→INSERT INTO specialties (id, name) VALUES (3, 'dentistry');\n    13→\n    14→-- Vet specialties\n    15→INSERT INTO vet_specialties (vet_id, specialty_id) VALUES (2, 1);\n    16→INSERT INTO vet_specialties (vet_id, specialty_id) VALUES (3, 2);\n    17→INSERT INTO vet_specialties (vet_id, specialty_id) VALUES (3, 3);\n    18→INSERT INTO vet_specialties (vet_id, specialty_id) VALUES (4, 2);\n    19→INSERT INTO vet_specialties (vet_id, specialty_id) VALUES (5, 1);\n    20→\n    21→-- Pet types\n    22→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (1, 'cat');\n    23→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (2, 'dog');\n    24→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (3, 'lizard');\n    25→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (4, 'snake');\n    26→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (5, 'bird');\n    27→INSERT INTO types (id, name) VALUES (6, 'hamster');\n    28→\n    29→-- Owners\n    30→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (1, 'George', 'Franklin', '110 W. Liberty St.', 'Madison', '6085551023');\n    31→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (2, 'Betty', 'Davis', '638 Cardinal Ave.', 'Sun Prairie', '6085551749');\n    32→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (3, 'Eduardo', 'Rodriquez', '2693 Commerce St.', 'McFarland', '6085558763');\n    33→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (4, 'Harold', 'Davis', '563 Friendly St.', 'Windsor', '6085553198');\n    34→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (5, 'Peter', 'McTavish', '2387 S. Fair Way', 'Madison', '6085552765');\n    35→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (6, 'Jean', 'Coleman', '105 N. Lake St.', 'Monona', '6085552654');\n    36→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (7, 'Jeff', 'Black', '1450 Oak Blvd.', 'Monona', '6085555387');\n    37→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (8, 'Maria', 'Escobito', '345 Maple St.', 'Madison', '6085557683');\n    38→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (9, 'David', 'Schroeder', '2749 Blackhawk Trail', 'Madison', '6085559435');\n    39→INSERT INTO owners (id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone) VALUES (10, 'Carlos', 'Estaban', '2335 Independence La.', 'Waunakee', '6085555487');\n    40→\n    41→-- Pets\n    42→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (1, 'Leo', '2010-09-07', 1, 1);\n    43→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (2, 'Basil', '2012-08-06', 6, 2);\n    44→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (3, 'Rosy', '2011-04-17', 2, 3);\n    45→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (4, 'Jewel', '2010-03-07', 2, 3);\n    46→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (5, 'Iggy', '2010-11-30', 3, 4);\n    47→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (6, 'George', '2010-01-20', 4, 5);\n    48→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (7, 'Samantha', '2012-09-04', 1, 6);\n    49→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (8, 'Max', '2012-09-04', 1, 6);\n    50→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (9, 'Lucky', '2011-08-06', 5, 7);\n    51→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (10, 'Mulligan', '2007-02-24', 2, 8);\n    52→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (11, 'Freddy', '2010-03-09', 5, 9);\n    53→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (12, 'Lucky', '2010-06-24', 2, 10);\n    54→INSERT INTO pets (id, name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id) VALUES (13, 'Sly', '2012-06-08', 1, 10);\n    55→\n    56→-- Visits\n    57→INSERT INTO visits (id, pet_id, visit_date, description) VALUES (1, 7, '2013-01-01', 'rabies shot');\n    58→INSERT INTO visits (id, pet_id, visit_date, description) VALUES (2, 8, '2013-01-02', 'rabies shot');\n    59→INSERT INTO visits (id, pet_id, visit_date, description) VALUES (3, 8, '2013-01-03', 'neutered');\n    60→INSERT INTO visits (id, pet_id, visit_date, description) VALUES (4, 7, '2013-01-04', 'spayed');\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"58dedac5-12aa-4911-a385-a7bc26d2fe24"}
