{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012YPiEhkFTore1ojRCkoqR4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.Optional;\n     7→\n     8→import io.quarkus.qute.Location;\n     9→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n    10→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    11→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    12→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n    14→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.BeanParam;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    20→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    21→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    23→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    24→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    25→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    26→\n    27→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    28→public class OwnerResource {\n    29→\n    30→\t@Inject\n    31→\tOwnerRepository ownerRepository;\n    32→\n    33→\t@Inject\n    34→\tValidator validator;\n    35→\n    36→\t@Inject\n    37→\t@Location(\"owners/findOwners.html\")\n    38→\tTemplate findOwners;\n    39→\n    40→\t@Inject\n    41→\t@Location(\"owners/ownersList.html\")\n    42→\tTemplate ownersList;\n    43→\n    44→\t@Inject\n    45→\t@Location(\"owners/ownerDetails.html\")\n    46→\tTemplate ownerDetails;\n    47→\n    48→\t@Inject\n    49→\t@Location(\"owners/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\")\n    50→\tTemplate createOrUpdateOwnerForm;\n    51→\n    52→\t@GET\n    53→\t@Path(\"/find\")\n    54→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    55→\tpublic TemplateInstance initFindForm() {\n    56→\t\treturn findOwners.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\");\n    57→\t}\n    58→\n    59→\t@GET\n    60→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    61→\tpublic Response processFindForm(\n    62→\t\t\t@QueryParam(\"page\") Integer page,\n    63→\t\t\t@QueryParam(\"lastName\") String lastName) {\n    64→\n    65→\t\tif (page == null) page = 1;\n    66→\t\tif (lastName == null) lastName = \"\";\n    67→\n    68→\t\tint pageSize = 5;\n    69→\t\tlong totalItems = ownerRepository.countByLastNameStartingWith(lastName);\n    70→\t\tList<Owner> owners = ownerRepository.findByLastNameStartingWith(lastName, page, pageSize);\n    71→\n    72→\t\tif (totalItems == 0) {\n    73→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = findOwners\n    74→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n    75→\t\t\t\t.data(\"error\", \"has not been found\")\n    76→\t\t\t\t.data(\"lastName\", lastName);\n    77→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n    78→\t\t}\n    79→\n    80→\t\tif (totalItems == 1) {\n    81→\t\t\tOwner owner = owners.get(0);\n    82→\t\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + owner.getId())).build();\n    83→\t\t}\n    84→\n    85→\t\tint totalPages = (int) Math.ceil((double) totalItems / pageSize);\n    86→\t\tList<Integer> pagesList = new ArrayList<>();\n    87→\t\tfor (int i = 1; i <= totalPages; i++) {\n    88→\t\t\tpagesList.add(i);\n    89→\t\t}\n    90→\n    91→\t\tTemplateInstance template = ownersList\n    92→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n    93→\t\t\t.data(\"listOwners\", owners)\n    94→\t\t\t.data(\"currentPage\", page)\n    95→\t\t\t.data(\"totalPages\", totalPages)\n    96→\t\t\t.data(\"totalItems\", totalItems)\n    97→\t\t\t.data(\"pages\", pagesList)\n    98→\t\t\t.data(\"lastName\", lastName);\n    99→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   100→\t}\n   101→\n   102→\t@GET\n   103→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n   104→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   105→\tpublic TemplateInstance initCreationForm() {\n   106→\t\tOwner owner = new Owner();\n   107→\t\treturn createOrUpdateOwnerForm\n   108→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   109→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   110→\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true);\n   111→\t}\n   112→\n   113→\t@POST\n   114→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n   115→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   116→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   117→\t@Transactional\n   118→\tpublic Response processCreationForm(\n   119→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n   120→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n   121→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n   122→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n   123→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone) {\n   124→\n   125→\t\tOwner owner = new Owner();\n   126→\t\towner.setFirstName(firstName);\n   127→\t\towner.setLastName(lastName);\n   128→\t\towner.setAddress(address);\n   129→\t\towner.setCity(city);\n   130→\t\towner.setTelephone(telephone);\n   131→\n   132→\t\tvar violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   133→\t\tif (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   134→\t\t\tList<ErrorInfo> errors = new ArrayList<>();\n   135→\t\t\tfor (ConstraintViolation<Owner> v : violations) {\n   136→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new ErrorInfo(v.getPropertyPath().toString(), v.getMessage()));\n   137→\t\t\t}\n   138→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdateOwnerForm\n   139→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   140→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   141→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true)\n   142→\t\t\t\t.data(\"errors\", errors);\n   143→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   144→\t\t}\n   145→\n   146→\t\townerRepository.save(owner);\n   147→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + owner.getId())).build();\n   148→\t}\n   149→\n   150→\t@GET\n   151→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId}\")\n   152→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   153→\tpublic Response showOwner(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId) {\n   154→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n   155→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n   156→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   157→\t\t}\n   158→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n   159→\t\tTemplateInstance template = ownerDetails\n   160→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   161→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner);\n   162→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   163→\t}\n   164→\n   165→\t@GET\n   166→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId}/edit\")\n   167→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   168→\tpublic Response initUpdateOwnerForm(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId) {\n   169→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n   170→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n   171→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   172→\t\t}\n   173→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n   174→\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdateOwnerForm\n   175→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   176→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   177→\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", false);\n   178→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   179→\t}\n   180→\n   181→\t@POST\n   182→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId}/edit\")\n   183→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   184→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   185→\t@Transactional\n   186→\tpublic Response processUpdateOwnerForm(\n   187→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n   188→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n   189→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n   190→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n   191→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n   192→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone) {\n   193→\n   194→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n   195→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n   196→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   197→\t\t}\n   198→\n   199→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n   200→\t\towner.setFirstName(firstName);\n   201→\t\towner.setLastName(lastName);\n   202→\t\towner.setAddress(address);\n   203→\t\towner.setCity(city);\n   204→\t\towner.setTelephone(telephone);\n   205→\n   206→\t\tvar violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   207→\t\tif (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   208→\t\t\tList<ErrorInfo> errors = new ArrayList<>();\n   209→\t\t\tfor (ConstraintViolation<Owner> v : violations) {\n   210→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new ErrorInfo(v.getPropertyPath().toString(), v.getMessage()));\n   211→\t\t\t}\n   212→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdateOwnerForm\n   213→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   214→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   215→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", false)\n   216→\t\t\t\t.data(\"errors\", errors);\n   217→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   218→\t\t}\n   219→\n   220→\t\townerRepository.save(owner);\n   221→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n   222→\t}\n   223→\n   224→\tpublic static class ErrorInfo {\n   225→\t\tpublic final String field;\n   226→\t\tpublic final String message;\n   227→\n   228→\t\tpublic ErrorInfo(String field, String message) {\n   229→\t\t\tthis.field = field;\n   230→\t\t\tthis.message = message;\n   231→\t\t}\n   232→\n   233→\t\tpublic String getField() {\n   234→\t\t\treturn field;\n   235→\t\t}\n   236→\n   237→\t\tpublic String getMessage() {\n   238→\t\t\treturn message;\n   239→\t\t}\n   240→\t}\n   241→\n   242→}\n   243→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"3670bab4-a491-4599-b50a-60eb66d4feda"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UUGtBTRMcBTc3gnSH89xKg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Optional;\n     8→\n     9→import io.quarkus.qute.Location;\n    10→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n    11→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    20→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    21→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    23→\n    24→@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId}/pets\")\n    25→public class PetResource {\n    26→\n    27→\t@Inject\n    28→\tOwnerRepository ownerRepository;\n    29→\n    30→\t@Inject\n    31→\tPetTypeRepository petTypeRepository;\n    32→\n    33→\t@Inject\n    34→\t@Location(\"pets/createOrUpdatePetForm.html\")\n    35→\tTemplate createOrUpdatePetForm;\n    36→\n    37→\t@GET\n    38→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    39→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    40→\tpublic Response initCreationForm(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId) {\n    41→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n    42→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n    43→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    44→\t\t}\n    45→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n    46→\t\tPet pet = new Pet();\n    47→\t\tList<PetType> types = petTypeRepository.findPetTypes();\n    48→\n    49→\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdatePetForm\n    50→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n    51→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    52→\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    53→\t\t\t.data(\"types\", types)\n    54→\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true);\n    55→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n    56→\t}\n    57→\n    58→\t@POST\n    59→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    60→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    61→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    62→\t@Transactional\n    63→\tpublic Response processCreationForm(\n    64→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    65→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"name\") String name,\n    66→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"birthDate\") String birthDateStr,\n    67→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"typeId\") Integer typeId) {\n    68→\n    69→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n    70→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n    71→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    72→\t\t}\n    73→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n    74→\t\tList<PetType> types = petTypeRepository.findPetTypes();\n    75→\n    76→\t\tPet pet = new Pet();\n    77→\t\tpet.setName(name);\n    78→\n    79→\t\tList<OwnerResource.ErrorInfo> errors = new ArrayList<>();\n    80→\n    81→\t\tif (name == null || name.isBlank()) {\n    82→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"name\", \"is required\"));\n    83→\t\t}\n    84→\n    85→\t\tif (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.isBlank()) {\n    86→\t\t\ttry {\n    87→\t\t\t\tLocalDate birthDate = LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr);\n    88→\t\t\t\tpet.setBirthDate(birthDate);\n    89→\t\t\t\tif (birthDate.isAfter(LocalDate.now())) {\n    90→\t\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"Birth date cannot be in the future\"));\n    91→\t\t\t\t}\n    92→\t\t\t} catch (Exception e) {\n    93→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"Invalid date format\"));\n    94→\t\t\t}\n    95→\t\t} else {\n    96→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"is required\"));\n    97→\t\t}\n    98→\n    99→\t\tif (typeId != null) {\n   100→\t\t\tPetType type = petTypeRepository.findById(typeId);\n   101→\t\t\tif (type != null) {\n   102→\t\t\t\tpet.setType(type);\n   103→\t\t\t} else {\n   104→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"type\", \"is required\"));\n   105→\t\t\t}\n   106→\t\t} else {\n   107→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"type\", \"is required\"));\n   108→\t\t}\n   109→\n   110→\t\tif (name != null && !name.isBlank() && owner.getPet(name, true) != null) {\n   111→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"name\", \"already exists\"));\n   112→\t\t}\n   113→\n   114→\t\tif (!errors.isEmpty()) {\n   115→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdatePetForm\n   116→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   117→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   118→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n   119→\t\t\t\t.data(\"types\", types)\n   120→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true)\n   121→\t\t\t\t.data(\"errors\", errors);\n   122→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   123→\t\t}\n   124→\n   125→\t\towner.addPet(pet);\n   126→\t\townerRepository.save(owner);\n   127→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n   128→\t}\n   129→\n   130→\t@GET\n   131→\t@Path(\"/{petId}/edit\")\n   132→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   133→\tpublic Response initUpdateForm(\n   134→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n   135→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId) {\n   136→\n   137→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n   138→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n   139→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   140→\t\t}\n   141→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n   142→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n   143→\t\tif (pet == null) {\n   144→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   145→\t\t}\n   146→\t\tList<PetType> types = petTypeRepository.findPetTypes();\n   147→\n   148→\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdatePetForm\n   149→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   150→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   151→\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n   152→\t\t\t.data(\"types\", types)\n   153→\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", false);\n   154→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   155→\t}\n   156→\n   157→\t@POST\n   158→\t@Path(\"/{petId}/edit\")\n   159→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   160→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   161→\t@Transactional\n   162→\tpublic Response processUpdateForm(\n   163→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n   164→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId,\n   165→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"name\") String name,\n   166→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"birthDate\") String birthDateStr,\n   167→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"typeId\") Integer typeId) {\n   168→\n   169→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n   170→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n   171→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   172→\t\t}\n   173→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n   174→\t\tPet existingPet = owner.getPet(petId);\n   175→\t\tif (existingPet == null) {\n   176→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   177→\t\t}\n   178→\t\tList<PetType> types = petTypeRepository.findPetTypes();\n   179→\n   180→\t\tList<OwnerResource.ErrorInfo> errors = new ArrayList<>();\n   181→\n   182→\t\tif (name == null || name.isBlank()) {\n   183→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"name\", \"is required\"));\n   184→\t\t}\n   185→\n   186→\t\tLocalDate birthDate = null;\n   187→\t\tif (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.isBlank()) {\n   188→\t\t\ttry {\n   189→\t\t\t\tbirthDate = LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr);\n   190→\t\t\t\tif (birthDate.isAfter(LocalDate.now())) {\n   191→\t\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"Birth date cannot be in the future\"));\n   192→\t\t\t\t}\n   193→\t\t\t} catch (Exception e) {\n   194→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"Invalid date format\"));\n   195→\t\t\t}\n   196→\t\t} else {\n   197→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"birthDate\", \"is required\"));\n   198→\t\t}\n   199→\n   200→\t\tPetType type = null;\n   201→\t\tif (typeId != null) {\n   202→\t\t\ttype = petTypeRepository.findById(typeId);\n   203→\t\t}\n   204→\n   205→\t\tif (!errors.isEmpty()) {\n   206→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdatePetForm\n   207→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   208→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   209→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", existingPet)\n   210→\t\t\t\t.data(\"types\", types)\n   211→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", false)\n   212→\t\t\t\t.data(\"errors\", errors);\n   213→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   214→\t\t}\n   215→\n   216→\t\texistingPet.setName(name);\n   217→\t\texistingPet.setBirthDate(birthDate);\n   218→\t\tif (type != null) {\n   219→\t\t\texistingPet.setType(type);\n   220→\t\t}\n   221→\t\townerRepository.save(owner);\n   222→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n   223→\t}\n   224→\n   225→}\n   226→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"c3b79ba8-4d5d-449d-91cf-e86174c01140"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TN8XLETy2bK9bsyUDTRpEq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Optional;\n     8→\n     9→import io.quarkus.qute.Location;\n    10→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n    11→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    20→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    21→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    23→\n    24→@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId}/pets/{petId}/visits\")\n    25→public class VisitResource {\n    26→\n    27→\t@Inject\n    28→\tOwnerRepository ownerRepository;\n    29→\n    30→\t@Inject\n    31→\t@Location(\"pets/createOrUpdateVisitForm.html\")\n    32→\tTemplate createOrUpdateVisitForm;\n    33→\n    34→\t@GET\n    35→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    36→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    37→\tpublic Response initNewVisitForm(\n    38→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    39→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId) {\n    40→\n    41→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n    42→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n    43→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    44→\t\t}\n    45→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n    46→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    47→\t\tif (pet == null) {\n    48→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    49→\t\t}\n    50→\n    51→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    52→\n    53→\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdateVisitForm\n    54→\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n    55→\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    56→\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    57→\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit);\n    58→\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n    59→\t}\n    60→\n    61→\t@POST\n    62→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    63→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    64→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    65→\t@Transactional\n    66→\tpublic Response processNewVisitForm(\n    67→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    68→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId,\n    69→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"date\") String dateStr,\n    70→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"description\") String description) {\n    71→\n    72→\t\tOptional<Owner> optionalOwner = ownerRepository.findById(ownerId);\n    73→\t\tif (optionalOwner.isEmpty()) {\n    74→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    75→\t\t}\n    76→\t\tOwner owner = optionalOwner.get();\n    77→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    78→\t\tif (pet == null) {\n    79→\t\t\treturn Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    80→\t\t}\n    81→\n    82→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    83→\t\tList<OwnerResource.ErrorInfo> errors = new ArrayList<>();\n    84→\n    85→\t\tif (dateStr != null && !dateStr.isBlank()) {\n    86→\t\t\ttry {\n    87→\t\t\t\tvisit.setDate(LocalDate.parse(dateStr));\n    88→\t\t\t} catch (Exception e) {\n    89→\t\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"date\", \"Invalid date format\"));\n    90→\t\t\t}\n    91→\t\t}\n    92→\n    93→\t\tif (description == null || description.isBlank()) {\n    94→\t\t\terrors.add(new OwnerResource.ErrorInfo(\"description\", \"must not be blank\"));\n    95→\t\t} else {\n    96→\t\t\tvisit.setDescription(description);\n    97→\t\t}\n    98→\n    99→\t\tif (!errors.isEmpty()) {\n   100→\t\t\tTemplateInstance template = createOrUpdateVisitForm\n   101→\t\t\t\t.data(\"activeMenu\", \"owners\")\n   102→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   103→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n   104→\t\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit)\n   105→\t\t\t\t.data(\"errors\", errors);\n   106→\t\t\treturn Response.ok(template).build();\n   107→\t\t}\n   108→\n   109→\t\tpet.addVisit(visit);\n   110→\t\townerRepository.save(owner);\n   111→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n   112→\t}\n   113→\n   114→}\n   115→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"3079fc2a-ad9b-40ed-88f8-e80e71696280"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012ByXzB51Tv9b8MGoPq7NQM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.model;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.MappedSuperclass;\n     9→\n    10→@MappedSuperclass\n    11→public class BaseEntity implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→\t@Id\n    14→\t@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    15→\tprivate Integer id;\n    16→\n    17→\tpublic Integer getId() {\n    18→\t\treturn id;\n    19→\t}\n    20→\n    21→\tpublic void setId(Integer id) {\n    22→\t\tthis.id = id;\n    23→\t}\n    24→\n    25→\tpublic boolean isNew() {\n    26→\t\treturn this.id == null;\n    27→\t}\n    28→\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"4e3b0e7a-ceb9-4d0e-9da3-c9ebcfc09209"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017ShUo4gZuwFehrzUqU2vP8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me fix all the issues. Here's my analysis:\n\n**Template fixes needed:**\n1. `ownerDetails.html`: `{#if message}` → `{#if message??}` (message is not always in data map)\n2. `createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html`: `{#if errors}` → `{#if errors??}` (errors only passed on validation failure)\n3. `createOrUpdatePetForm.html`: `{#if errors}` → `{#if errors??}`, `{#if pet.id}` → `{#if pet.id??}` (new pets have null id)\n4. `createOrUpdateVisitForm.html`: `{#if errors}` → `{#if errors??}`\n5. `ownersList.html`: `{lastName ?: ''}` → `{lastName.orEmpty}` (to be safe)\n\n**import.sql fix:** With `GenerationType.IDENTITY`, H2 auto-generates IDs. Inserting explicit IDs causes conflicts. Need to remove explicit ID columns from inserts, but we need stable IDs for foreign key references. The solution is to use `SET` statements to control the identity column start value, or restructure to not specify IDs but rely on insertion order with `ALTER TABLE` sequences.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for H2 with IDENTITY is to insert without specifying the `id` column but in correct order, so auto-generated IDs match. Let me apply all fixes now:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8751,"cache_read_input_tokens":31367,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8751,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1762},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"a70eeef6-0899-4350-8583-490e44a64658"}
