{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XCWeaTpFJG437gnAxzKpQ4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collection;\n     5→import java.util.LinkedHashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→\n     8→import org.springframework.samples.petclinic.model.NamedEntity;\n     9→\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    13→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    15→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    16→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    17→import jakarta.persistence.OrderBy;\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    19→\n    20→@Entity\n    21→@Table(name = \"pets\")\n    22→public class Pet extends NamedEntity {\n    23→\n    24→\t@Column(name = \"birth_date\")\n    25→\tprivate LocalDate birthDate;\n    26→\n    27→\t@ManyToOne\n    28→\t@JoinColumn(name = \"type_id\")\n    29→\tprivate PetType type;\n    30→\n    31→\t@OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    32→\t@JoinColumn(name = \"pet_id\")\n    33→\t@OrderBy(\"date ASC\")\n    34→\tprivate Set<Visit> visits = new LinkedHashSet<>();\n    35→\n    36→\tpublic void setBirthDate(LocalDate birthDate) {\n    37→\t\tthis.birthDate = birthDate;\n    38→\t}\n    39→\n    40→\tpublic LocalDate getBirthDate() {\n    41→\t\treturn this.birthDate;\n    42→\t}\n    43→\n    44→\tpublic PetType getType() {\n    45→\t\treturn this.type;\n    46→\t}\n    47→\n    48→\tpublic void setType(PetType type) {\n    49→\t\tthis.type = type;\n    50→\t}\n    51→\n    52→\tpublic Collection<Visit> getVisits() {\n    53→\t\treturn this.visits;\n    54→\t}\n    55→\n    56→\tpublic void addVisit(Visit visit) {\n    57→\t\tgetVisits().add(visit);\n    58→\t}\n    59→\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1bfca6e-e423-4132-a6e2-418ea88669ae","uuid":"c054748f-423f-4f25-b2b3-abdd2e57d819"}
